description: From Italian (Venetian dialect) regatta (“contention for mastery”), from regattare (“compete, haggle, sell at retail”), possibly from ricattare; or from Italian regata (“boat race, regatta”), via Vulgar Latin *aurigata from Latin auriga.

nouns.description: regatta (countable and uncountable, plural regattas or regatte)

entries.meaning: (countable) A series of boat races, or sometimes a single race.
